title: Fellowship Guide
author: UnknownOreo1996
pages:
#- Introduction
-------------------

Welcome to Fellowship! We're a bustling city located at 6100, -2800 boasting over 50 citizens. Within this guide you'll be able to learn all about this wonderful town!

/r/CivcraftFellowship
#- Citizenship
-------------------

Becoming a citizen of Fellowship is simple! All you have to do is sign the "Citizenship Thread" which can be found on /r/CivcraftFellowship.
(Look under "Important Links" on the sidebar.)
#- Getting a Home!
-------------------

To acquire a home within Fellowship all you have to do is ask a government member or Fellow, they will be able to direct you to one of the free plots avaliable at the top of the Hexagon.
#- Government
-------------------

Fellowship is run by a series of Ministers and a pair of Diarchs. One diarch is elected while the other is permanent. To be able to partake in elections and government functions you must become a "Fellow" which means...
#- Government Cont.
-------------------

... that you have lived within Fellowship for three weeks and have been accepted by all current Fellows.
#- Laws & Rules
-------------------

1. Do not kill unless given permission or if you're attacking a known offender of the law.

2. Do not steal.

3. Do not assault others.
#- Laws & Rules Cont.
-------------------

4. Do not trespass within private property of others without permission.

5. Do not grief others with blocks, fire, words, etc. Please do not use obscenities in excess.
#- Rights
-------------------

1. All individuals have a right to a home.

2. All individuals have a right to private property.

3. All individuals have the right to basic reinforcement mats.
#- Rights Cont.
-------------------

4. All individuals have the right to appeal legal matters to the Diarchs and the Ministry.
#- 